Elheist steers deep‑cuts, left‑field electronica, obscure grooves and sounds from the fam into the fold, where worlds collide, textures shift and surprises hit. check your quest, leave the rest.

From the host: "First time back after maternity leave for the final show of 2025. No chat this time, just tunes!"

Artist, graphic designer and DJ Paul Camo sets out to push the boundaries: free of all restrictions. Jump in the chat and listen as Paul Camo's WE ARE brings you on a voyage through the spectrum of jazz fusion, spiritual jazz, experimental jazz and everything in between.
Sounds of the Dawn is a monthly two hour session through new age, ambient, environmental, meditation and relaxation cassettes from the seventies to the nineties. Tune in and zone out.

nts2.d: Beloved Mauritanian griot, singer and multi-instrumentalist Noura Mint Seymali selects an hour of original music and inspirations, including tracks from Youssou N’dour, Pharoah Sanders, Anita Baker and more.
Broadcasting out of Birmingham, Arrhythmia is a monthly exploration of interesting new audio and abnormal rhythms. Expect irregular, dark or heavy - but not always.

Exploring the cinematic universe inhabited by Japanese director Hirokazu Kore-eda, master of shomin-geki, the technique of magnifying small but significant human moments on film as opposed to grand dramatic conflict and tension. 
“I’ve learned to value ordinary life. And I still have a wish to portray that.”
Kaifeng based DJ & producer Yu Su cooks up an hour of warm meanderings once a month.

The breezy sound of the Canadian Riviera, from Mood Hut's Pender Street Steppers.
From the host: "PSS is joined in the mix by Second Spring, a collective of artists, musicians and curators based out of Vancouver and Toronto."
Brooklyn musician Nick Hakim takes over the NTS airwaves.

nts2.n: La Danza del Selector w/ backyardmango
nts2.d: Colourful Latin dancefloor selections from Mexican-American DJ & record head backyardmango.
Ahwlee & Pink Siifu (B. Cool-Aid) head up BRWN, exploring hip hop's varied and far-reaching experimental corners - live once a month from Los Angeles.

nts2.n: West Coast Fog: Ode To The Whale Folk
nts2.d:
West Coast Fog with Erik Bluhm, broadcasts monthly from far-flung natural environments, bringing along site specific, privately released meditational music from past decades for a deeply involved sensory experience.
From the host: "Join West Coast Fog asea, at anchor, and eventually ashore. Sail with whales and listen to serene marine sounds from '80s and '90s cassettes."

nts2.n: Word of Command - Live from Drama Radio Bar, CDMX
nts2.d: DJ, artist and techno impresario, Word of Command welds fevered collage and high-octane techno into a hallucinatory dreamscape. He is the founder of FIST (@funisstilltransgressive), a queer techno party that pays tribute to radical fun, while engaging the visibility of communities of otherness through techno in NYC.
TRiNH - an hour of covers and nostalgic feels, playing a wide range of genres with a focus on L-O-V-E.
Cuban record collector, ethnomusicologist researcher, picks up a hour of global vinyl via Havana every months.
Forager Records is a Los Angeles based record label, committed to unearthing and breathing new life into rare and under appreciated sounds from the past.
A Colourful Storm from label head Moopie, featuring contemplative ambience, folksong and indie-pop melancholia, contemporary electronics and beyond.
Avant-garde musician and composer Jim O'Rourke pulls stops by once a month, pulling an hour of picks from his extensive record collection.
Irish musician Olan Monk joins for a guest show playing songs and instrumentals, from sean-nós to shoegaze, that surround and ground their latest album Songs for Nothing, out now on AD 93.
Montreal-based contemporary classical pianist and songwriter Laurie Torres stops by the London studio.

Rebe, the only official Princess of Spain, sentimental hijacking now in the radio format. Playing Romanian and Spanish folk, flamenco pop, soundtracks, originals and many more mysteries. Radio-Rebe, Radio-Ready’s worst nightmare.

subtle.d: Rolling through varied tempo's and genres, Jimmy 2 Shoes brings dance floor orientated vibes and flows to wriggle your toes to. Expect eclectic selections and the freshest sounds from the UK underground.

As if kid is a professional Producer, DJ and Drummer from the west country (UK). Real name "Sid", He is versatile in producing hot records in various genres: Grime, UK Drill, Hip Hop, Jungle and more with an ever-growing number of global commercial placements and releases. He regularly collaborates with DJ Slimzee under alias E3 Breaks and with DJ Raggs under the alias Slamfire!

subtle.n: The Wheel Up Show w/ Tripta
subtle.d: Tripta is a Toronto based producer/DJ focusing on the darker sounds of Grime. Also blending elements of Drill, Dubstep and even Jungle all together for a unique sound you won't hear anywhere else. Signed to Slimzee's 'Slimzo's Recordings' and ‘Rotpot Records’.

Sound Arkitek is a Chicago hip-hop DJ with a love for all things drum & bass. 

With over 20 years experience playing house parties, raves, clubs and bars he has an encyclopedic knowledge of music but has always been a participant in jungle culture. In the early 2000s he was exposed to the genre primarily through Dieselboy and Danny The Wildchild mixes as well as the “Jungle Book” series of mixtapes. He became obsessed after hearing Bad Company’s “The Nine” and “Four Days,” as well as Pendulum’s “Vault.” 

As time went on, he got deeper into the scene, going to raves while buying records and posting on Drum & Bass Arena and DNBForum before turning 21 at which point he began going to Lava Lounge for Bass By The Pound’s “Seminar” series. The first legal drum & bass party he attended was Chase & Status at the aforementioned Lava Lounge, and he will never forget the energy when the duo played DJ Hazard’s “Killers Don’t Die” and it got a rewind. His love for the scene led to him playing drum & bass parties, opening for artists like Original Sin, Gridlok, and LTJ Bukem among others. 

His Subtle Radio show is an hour of the finest tunes in the scene at the moment. 

To keep up, follow @djsoundarkitek on Instagram!

Darcy is 23 year old DJ from Bristol who specialises in dubstep and grime. With a love for choppy techniques and old school grime cyphers, her sounds create a unique energy that reflect in her sets and mixes. 

New to the scene, she has played alongside 140 legends like Just Jane, White Peach Records, Riz la Teef and more. Working closely with underground labels like Partum Audio, as well as curating a montly show for her residency on Mondo Radio- Darcy continues to develop her style and make her name.

subtle.d: Dubversified showcases Canadian West Coast DJ talent specializing in Bass Music. Hosted by Mirage, founder of Dubversified Culture, a community-led organization focusing on music, art, and events. Mirage, originally from Québec, blends house and hip-hop since 2010, now exploring 140bpm and Deep D&B.

subtle.n: Into The Lion's Den w/ Restrikt

subtle.d: Potent Funk records’ Matt Frost - Well known for his technical abilities and Sleazy bass music style, Frost covers all angles from UK alt Rap to the LA beat scene.

Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

Originally from Cambridge, Counter Culture's selection deftly navigates across a myriad of influences and exclusives from himself & friends.
Expect some of the freshest rolling soul straight to your headspace.

subtle.n: Strictly Business Show w/ Qua Rush & Flipz MC
5 Decades of Dub w/ Joe Vincent

subtle.d: casual_observer is a DJ and producer originally hailing from Amsterdam, where he co-organises the "moving closer" event series with friend and collaborator Bcl-2. He currently resides in Berlin. Starting his musical journey as a drummer, his music retains a heavy focus on groove, rhythm and experimentation.  Sets played by casual_observer are diverse and surprising, moving effortlessly between jungle, breaks, bass, footwork, and more. No matter the genre, his selection is sure to keep you on your toes!

In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.

subtle.n: THE CULTURE HEAD w. SAINT VOX

subtle.d: DIGDIS presents a selection of tracks that captures the vibrant and ever-evolving edges of dance music. Each show features a wide range of music that can be enjoyed both on the dancefloor and in more intimate listening spaces.

My show focuses on percussive, club sounds, taking inspiration from the edges of drill, funky and bass music. In both my mixes and productions, I like to keep the energy high and a little whimsical. Expect some moments of ambient and R&B too, just so we can all catch our breath.
